page.title: 10Interview With Mr.Wilks
page.content: Mr Wilks is 76 years old. He has lived in Tiptree all his life and enjoys it. Mr Wilks seems to have a high opinion of Tiptree. He says that he preferred 1985 to 1920, because there are more people and he is not as lonely. At the beginning of his life he was one of 300 people living in Tiptree . There were thirteen pubs. Now there are only six Pubs and around 10,000 people. Mr Wilks thinks that Tiptree is no more peaceful than it was in 1930. He said that his ancestors lived in Tiptree during the 16th century and have lived there ever since. Mr Wilks thinks that the police force should become better because there is more technology. He also thinks that living in Tiptree in 1985 would be better if the council would run things more smoothly.
